import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    yearly_disasters = data.groupby(['Year', 'Entity']).size().reset_index(name='Count')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=yearly_disasters, x='Year', y='Count', hue='Entity')
    plt.title('What is the trend of natural disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Disaster Type', loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    
    total_deaths_by_disaster = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    total_deaths_by_disaster = total_deaths_by_disaster.sort_values('Deaths', ascending=False)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='Entity', y='Deaths', data=total_deaths_by_disaster)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('Which type of natural disaster has caused the most deaths?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend(title='Disaster Types', loc='upper right', labels=total_deaths_by_disaster['Entity'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Deaths', bins=50, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['Deaths'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['Deaths'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of deaths caused by natural disasters?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Deaths")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    yearly_deaths = data.groupby('Year')['Deaths'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=yearly_deaths)
    plt.axhline(yearly_deaths['Deaths'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Average: {yearly_deaths['Deaths'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the average number of deaths caused by natural disasters per year?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
